<subSubSection id="C3246572FF9CC933FF62FF1DFBE0FF16" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF9CC933FF62FF1DFBE0FF16" blockId="61.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF9CC933FF62FF1DFEC0FF72" bold="true" box="[199,334,151,177]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the businessman Ariosto da Riva, who in the early 70’s acquired the region currently known as Alta Floresta, to start a new settlement project; genitive case.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3246572FF9CC933FF62FF54FF65FE82" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF9CC933FF62FF54FF65FE82" blockId="61.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF9CC933FF62FF54FECCFF3B" bold="true" box="[199,322,222,248]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFF9CC933FE6AFF55FDA4FF3B" authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[463,554,223,248]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rivai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF9CC933FE6AFF55FDA4FF3B" box="[463,554,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">M. rivai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF9CC933FD96FF55FD00FF3A" bold="true" box="[563,654,223,249]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FF9CC933FD96FF55FD00FF3A" box="[563,654,223,249]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
are distinguished from the remaining congeners by the epigyne with MS Erlenmeyer-shaped (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF9CC933FE13FE89FD94FEDE" box="[438,538,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 238–244" captionStartId="59.[151,264,1821,1845]" captionTargetBox="[190,1385,470,1788]" captionTargetId="figure-83@59.[186,1401,453,1797]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURES 238–244. 238–241 Meri quinari spec. nov., male (UFMG 10165), left palp (238 prolateral, 239 ventral, 240 retrolateral, 241 detail of embolus); 242–244 Meri rivai spec. nov., female (IBSP 246428) (242 epigyne, 243 vulva, 244 schematic course of internal duct system). db—dorsal branch of RTA; E—embolus; EP—epigynal pocket; ft—first turn f duct system; FD—fertilization duct; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MAB—muscle attachment bands; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SdP—subdistal projection; SP—spermathecae. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550494" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550494/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Fig. 242</figureCitation>
) and vulva with SP elongate with smooth margins (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF9CC933FBDFFE89FB6BFEDE" box="[1146,1253,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 238–244" captionStartId="59.[151,264,1821,1845]" captionTargetBox="[190,1385,470,1788]" captionTargetId="figure-83@59.[186,1401,453,1797]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURES 238–244. 238–241 Meri quinari spec. nov., male (UFMG 10165), left palp (238 prolateral, 239 ventral, 240 retrolateral, 241 detail of embolus); 242–244 Meri rivai spec. nov., female (IBSP 246428) (242 epigyne, 243 vulva, 244 schematic course of internal duct system). db—dorsal branch of RTA; E—embolus; EP—epigynal pocket; ft—first turn f duct system; FD—fertilization duct; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MAB—muscle attachment bands; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SdP—subdistal projection; SP—spermathecae. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550494" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550494/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Figs 243</figureCitation>
). Males are unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3246572FF9CC933FF62FEC0FE0AFDA2" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF9CC933FF62FEC0FC15FDFE" blockId="61.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF9CC933FF62FEC0FDCDFEA7" bold="true" box="[199,579,330,357]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
Description. Female (
<typeStatus id="5485885BFF9CC933FE6DFEC0FDB8FEA7" box="[456,566,330,356]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">holotype</typeStatus>
):
</emphasis>
Total length 17.6. Prosoma 6.8 long, 6.8 wide. Opisthosoma 10.7 long, 7.5 wide. Eyes: diameters: 0.46, 0.41, 0.30, 0.36; interdistances: 0.47, 0.38, 0.84, 0.81, 0.43, 0.28. Legs: I: 27.0 (7.5, 3.3, 6.8, 7.3, 2.1); 28.6 (8.6, 3.5, 7.0, 7.5, 2.0); III: 21.0 (6.6, 2.9, 5.0, 4.9, 1.6); IV: 22.8 (7.2, 2.6, 5.4, 5.8, 1.8). Spination follows the generic pattern. Epigyne: EF wider than long; MAB elongate; MS longer than wide, widest posteriorly; HP triangular, 1.5 times longer than wide, opening at posterior margin of MS; LL touching posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF9CC933FF3AFE75FE88FDDA" box="[159,262,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURES 238–244" captionStartId="59.[151,264,1821,1845]" captionTargetBox="[190,1385,470,1788]" captionTargetId="figure-83@59.[186,1401,453,1797]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURES 238–244. 238–241 Meri quinari spec. nov., male (UFMG 10165), left palp (238 prolateral, 239 ventral, 240 retrolateral, 241 detail of embolus); 242–244 Meri rivai spec. nov., female (IBSP 246428) (242 epigyne, 243 vulva, 244 schematic course of internal duct system). db—dorsal branch of RTA; E—embolus; EP—epigynal pocket; ft—first turn f duct system; FD—fertilization duct; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MAB—muscle attachment bands; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SdP—subdistal projection; SP—spermathecae. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550494" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550494/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Figs 242</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF9CC933FEB7FE75FECEFDDA" box="[274,320,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURES 245–249" captionStartId="60.[151,264,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[157,1424,1113,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-352@60.[151,1435,1101,1941]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURES 245–249. 245–247 Meri quinari spec. nov., male (UFMG 10165, holotype), left palp (245 prolateral, 246 ventral, 247 retrolateral); 248–249 Meri rivai spec. nov., female (IBSP 246428, holotype) (248 epigyne, 249 vulva). Scale lines 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550496" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550496/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">248</figureCitation>
). Vulva: internal ducts with FW antero laterad; GP slightly longer than wide, mediad, arising from ducts at first turn; FD anteriad to antero-laterad (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF9CC933FD1DFDA9FCDBFDFE" box="[696,853,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 238–244" captionStartId="59.[151,264,1821,1845]" captionTargetBox="[190,1385,470,1788]" captionTargetId="figure-83@59.[186,1401,453,1797]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURES 238–244. 238–241 Meri quinari spec. nov., male (UFMG 10165), left palp (238 prolateral, 239 ventral, 240 retrolateral, 241 detail of embolus); 242–244 Meri rivai spec. nov., female (IBSP 246428) (242 epigyne, 243 vulva, 244 schematic course of internal duct system). db—dorsal branch of RTA; E—embolus; EP—epigynal pocket; ft—first turn f duct system; FD—fertilization duct; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MAB—muscle attachment bands; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SdP—subdistal projection; SP—spermathecae. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550494" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550494/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Figs 243–244</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF9CC933FCC5FDA9FC00FDFE" box="[864,910,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 245–249" captionStartId="60.[151,264,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[157,1424,1113,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-352@60.[151,1435,1101,1941]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURES 245–249. 245–247 Meri quinari spec. nov., male (UFMG 10165, holotype), left palp (245 prolateral, 246 ventral, 247 retrolateral); 248–249 Meri rivai spec. nov., female (IBSP 246428, holotype) (248 epigyne, 249 vulva). Scale lines 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550496" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550496/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">249</figureCitation>
